<head>
<title>PR 10/10/96 Strawberry workers, UFW president, to visit
East Coast leaders</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<p>For information: Richard Greer, AFL-CIO, 202-637-5279<br>
Jocelyn Sherman, UFW, 408-763-4907<br>
<br>
<br>
NEWS MEDIA ADVISORY<br>
<br>
Strawberry workers, UFW president, to visit East Coast leaders<br>
<br>
Washington, Oct. 10, 1996 -- United Farm Workers President Arturo<br>
Rodriquez and California strawberry workers will visit key<br>
religious, political and community leaders in six East Coast<br>
cities in November.<br>
<br>
The purpose of the trip is to solidify support for 20,000<br>
strawberry workers, who are seeking basic rights such as clean<br>
drinking water and bathrooms, a living wage and protection from<br>
sexual harassment in the fields.<br>
<br>
The workers_ struggle is one of the largest union organizing<br>
campaigns in the U.S. It is a joint project of the UFW and the<br>
AFL-CIO.<br>
<br>
The trip will begin a week after a broad-based coalition of<br>
dozens of groups that support the strawberry workers meets in<br>
Washington. The workers believe 5 cents is not too much to ask<br>
for fairness -- a California study showed that for 5 cents more<br>
per pint of berries, workers' pay rates would increase by at
least 50<br>
percent. But, so far, the $650 million-a-year strawberry industry<br>
isn_t interested.<br>
<br>
Below is the tentative schedule for the workers.<br>
* Nov. 18: Philadelphia<br>
* Nov. 19: Baltimore<br>
* Nov. 20: Newark<br>
* Nov. 21: New York City<br>
* Nov. 22: Boston<br>
* Nov. 23-24: Washington<br>
<br>
News conferences will be held in each city and there may be<br>
opportunities for individual interviews with the workers and<br>
Rodriguez. More details will be announced as the event<br>
approaches.</p>
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a
href="../index.htm">Public Documents Page</a> | <a
href="../publsear.htm">Public Documents Search</a></p>
