<p>Media Advisory For information: Rich Greer, 202/637-5279<br>
August 29, 1996 or Deborah Dion at 202/637-5036<br>
<br>
LABOR DAY WEEKEND AGENDA<br>
HISTORIC SPEECH TO STRAWBERRY WORKERS, DETROIT MARCH<br>
Events also in Wisconsin, California, Illinois, New Jersey<br>
<br>
AFL-CIO officers will participate in activities around the<br>
nation on Labor Day weekend. Among the activities are a picket to<br>
support striking Detroit newspaper workers and an appearance by<br>
President John J. Sweeney before the United Farm Workers
convention<br>
in Fresno, Calif.<br>
<br>
Sweeney will be the first AFL-CIO president to address a<br>
convention of the farm workers, who have begun an organizing
drive<br>
among 20,000 strawberry workers. It is the largest organizing
drive<br>
in the U.S. today.<br>
