<title>PR 08/26/962 Working Family Agenda</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<p>MEDIA ADVISORY<br>
<br>
<br>
ADVISORY FOR AUGUST 23-29 Contact: Deborah Dion/David Saltz at<br>
DEMOCRATIC NATIONAL CONVENTION (312) 819-9356 or 57<br>
Dion/888-858-7243 Pin 100810<br>
Saltz/202-424-4191 or Pin 104898<br>
<br>
AFL-CIO BRINGS WORKING FAMILIES' AGENDA TO CHICAGO;<br>
OVER 800 DELEGATES ATTEND DEMOCRATIC CONVENTION<br>
<br>
Chicago -- Over 800 AFL-CIO delegates representing forty-one<br>
International Unions will converge in Chicago next week at the<br>
Democratic National Convention to speak out on issues that are<br>
important to working families and jobs, affordable health care,<br>
secure pensions and quality education, and respect for working.<br>
<br>
During the week AFL-CIO delegates will attend caucus meetings,<br>
political and educational workshops and will have a clear voice
on<br>
the convention floor. The Highlight of the week will be an<br>
&quot;American Needs A Raise&quot; Rally on Monday, August 26th
at Noon. <br>
John Sweeney, President of the AFL-CIO will join thousands of<br>
workers, community and religious leaders at the State of Illinois<br>
Building to protest corporate greed and the ever-growing wage gap<br>
between the rich and the rest of America. Sweeney will tell<br>
corporate America and Congress that the labor movement is ready
to<br>
respond as never before to the pressures on working families by<br>
stopping the assault on working families and restoring respect
for<br>
workers and their contributions.<br>
<br>
The AFL-CIO offices are located in Wacker Hall at the Hyatt<br>
Regency Chicago. Wacker Hall is in the East Tower of the Hyatt in<br>
the lower level (Exhibition Level). The AFL-CIO will also have a<br>
space in the United Center Media Tent (TBD).<br>
<br>
If you would like to set up interviews with John Sweeney, Richard<br>
Trumka, Linda Chavez-Thompson or any of the AFL-CIO delegates<br>
please call Deborah Dion or David Saltz.<br>
<br>
WE WILL NOTIFY PRESS OF OTHER AFL-CIO ACTIVITIES DAILY.</p>
