<title>PR 03/04/96 Terrorist bombings in Israel</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<h3 align="center">STATEMENT BY AFL-CIO PRESIDENT JOHN J. SWEENEY<br>
ON THE RECENT TERRORIST BOMBINGS IN ISRAEL </h3>
<p>I want to express my deepest condolences to the people of
Israel in the aftermath of the horrible series of bombings in the
last week that have taken so many innocent lives. </p>
<p>The American people have stood with Israel in many difficult
times through its short but troubled history these past 47 years,
and we will continue to do so as Israel wrestles with momentous
challenges and choices in pursuit of a secure and peaceful life
in a dangerous neighborhood. </p>
<p>This is a day for mourning, but in the days ahead crucial
political decisions will be made. The U.S. must do everything
possible to help Israel combat the scourge of international
terrorism. We must not allow radical extremists to hijack the
hope for peace that millions long for and for which so many,
including Yitzhak Rabin, gave their lives. </p>
<p>It's difficult to see it on a day like this, but history
ultimately is on the side of the peacemakers. Unfortunately, the
road to peace in the Middle East is a rough one that requires
those of us who believe in it to struggle and fight to bring it
about. Let us pray that day will come soon.</p>
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a
href="../index.htm">Public Documents Page</a> | <a
href="../publsear.htm">Public Documents Search</a></p>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; AFL-CIO</p>
</body>
