<body>
<h2 align="center">Media Advisory for AFL-CIO Executive Council
Meeting<br>
February 19-22</h2>
<pre>
For Immediate Release

               For Information: Deborah Dion (202/898-3266)
                                Beginning Sunday, 2/18, at the
                                Sheraton Bal Harbour 305/865-7511
</pre>
<h3 align="center">AFL-CIO Unions Advance New Initiatives in
Organizing, Economic Education and Political Action To Turn
Around Working Families' Decline </h3>
<p>Washington, D.C. -- New initiatives in organizing, economic
education and political action will dominate discussion at the
AFL- CIO Executive Council meeting in Bal Harbour, Fla., February
19 - 22. </p>
<p>Three weeks ago, Sweeney appointed Richard Bensinger to head
up the AFL-CIO's new Organizing Department. On Monday morning
Sweeney will outline plans for an aggressive organizing strategy.
Executive Council members will also hear from workers and
organizers who will speak about the need for a strong organizing
program. </p>
<p>On Tuesday Sweeney will release a schedule of town hall
meetings to listen to workers' concerns and ideas about declining
living standards -- part of a new &quot;America Needs a
Raise&quot; public education initiative. And on Wednesday the
council will discuss plans for 1996 legislative and political
action. </p>
<p>Several guests will also address the council meeting
including: Vice President Al Gore, Secretary of Labor Robert
Reich, Secretary of Treasury Robert Rubin, Minority Leader
Richard Gephardt (D-3rd Mo.), Minority Whip David Bonior (D-10th
Mich.) and Children's Defense Fund President Marian Wright
Edelman. </p>
<pre>
Press events include (Note: Times are tentative):

Monday, February 19

7:00 - 8:00 a.m.    Press Breakfast: John Sweeney, Rich Trumka and
                    Linda Chavez-Thompson (Room TBA)

12:00 noon          Congressman David Bonior Press Availability

12:15 p.m.          Press Briefing: Rebuilding the Labor Movement
                    -- John Sweeney, Arthur A. Coia, Richard
                    Bensinger

2:30 p.m.*          Congressman Richard Gephardt Press
                    Availability

4:00 p.m.           Vice President Al Gore Press Availability

Tuesday, February 20

8:30 a.m.           United Farm Workers Press Conference

10:00 a.m.          Secretary of Labor Robert Reich Press
                    Conference

12:15 p.m.          Press Briefing: &quot;American Needs a Raise&quot; Town
                    Hall Meetings -- John Sweeney

2:30 p.m.*          Secretary of the Treasury Robert Rubin Press
                    Availability (if schedule permits)

4:00 - 6:00 p.m.    National Council of Senior Citizens/AFL-CIO
                    Rally Against Medicare/Social Security Cuts at
                    the Sheraton Bal Harbour

Wednesday, February 21

10:00 a.m.          Marian Wright Edelman, Children's Defense Fund

12:15 p.m.          Press Briefing: Political Action -- John
                    Sweeney, Gerald McEntee and AFL-CIO Political
                    Director Steve Rosenthal

*Tentative press availability</pre>
