<html>
<head>
<title>PR 02/02/96 Overturn Exec Order</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE FEB. 2, 1996      FOR INFORMATION CONTACT:
                                   Candice Johnson, 202/637-5010
</pre>
<h3 align="center">Statement by John J. Sweeney, President,
AFL-CIO, on the federal appeals court decision to overturn
President Clinton's executive order on the permanent replacement
of striking workers: </h3>
<p>Today's decision by the District of Columbia Court of Appeals
to overturn President Clinton's executive order barring federal
contracts to employers who permanently replace their workers is
simply wrong as a matter of policy and of law. This ruling serves
those employers who want to wage war on workers, and hurts the
rest of us -- working families, communities, fair employers, our
nation. </p>
<p>Until President Reagan fired the air traffic controllers in
1981, it was almost unheard of for employers to punish workers
for exercising their right to strike. Everyone understood that
doing so was wrong. </p>
<p>Now, three judges appointed by Presidents Reagan and Bush have
declared that firing strikers is right, and that even the
President of the United States cannot refuse to do business with
federal contractors who throw out their experienced, skilled
employees and replace them with workers who often are poorly
prepared. </p>
<p>We will fight against this decision -- and every attack on
American working families.</p>
