<title>PR 01/03/96 Government Shutdown</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>                                        For information, contact:
                                   Sharolyn Rosier (202) 637-5010
For Release Wednesday, Jan 3, 1995
</pre>
<h3 align="center">Statement on Government Shutdown by John J.
Sweeney, president, AFL-CIO: </h3>
<p>Federal employees do not deserve to be treated as pawns by
House Republicans, who continue to hold current government
functions hostage in order to force long-term cuts in education,
Medicare, Medicaid and other programs that serve working families
- while they award massive tax breaks to the rich. </p>
<p>The American public must ask whether members of Congress, with
salaries of $133,600, care that thousands of federal employees
cannot pay their bills and feed their children without a
paycheck. Meanwhile, job safety and health hazards go unchecked,
children's toys are not inspected, federal housing loans are not
processed and applications for college loans and grants are
sitting on federal workers' desks. </p>
<p>To help federal workers, the AFL-CIO has worked with the
American Federation of Government Employees to create a $5
million fund to provide federal workers with low- or no-interest
loans. </p>
<p>Congress should act responsibly, in the interests of the
American taxpayers who pay their salaries and the federal
employees who do the real work of administering national
programs.</p>
