<title>PR 11/14/95 Statement on Government Shutdown</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>	        	                   For further information:
        	        	           Denise Mitchell (202) 637-5340
</pre>
<h3 align="center">Statement on Government Shutdown<br>
by John J. Sweeney, president AFLCIO </h3>
<p>We condemn Republican Congressional leaders for using Federal
workers as pawns in a cruel budget game designed to circumvent
the wishes of the American people. And we commend President
Clinton for standing firm against massive cuts in Medicare,
Medicaid, student loans and other vital programs: 61 percent of
the voters want him to reject the Republican budget. The AFL-CIO
will support the locked-out workers with every resource at our
command and we will resist this attempt at budget blackmail with
every weapon at our disposal. </p>
<p align="center">### </p>
