<html>
<head>
<title>PR 11/08/95 AFL-CIO against proposed GOP Budget</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>Media advisory for Wednesday, Nov. 8                   Contact: Candice Johnson
                                                                202/637-5010
</pre>
<h4 align="center">First Washington appearance by new AFL-CIO
Executive Vice President<br>
Linda Chavez-Thompson is Wednesday, Nov. 8, across from the White
House. <br>
</h4>
<h3 align="center">Chavez-Thompson Leads Rally Against Proposed
GOP Budget </h3>
<p>Linda Chavez-Thompson, the AFL-CIO's new executive vice
president and the first person of color to hold an executive
office at the 13-million-member AFL-CIO, will make her first
Washington appearance at a noon rally on Wednesday, Nov. 8, in
Lafayette Park. She will lead the crowd in voicing support for
President Clinton's commitment to veto the proposed GOP budget. </p>
<p>Chavez-Thompson was elected a top officer of the labor
federation last month, part of the AFL-CIO's new leadership team
that also includes President John J. Sweeney and
SecretaryTreasurer Richard Trumka. The team was elected following
a sixmonth campaign to bring ``a new voice for American
workers.'' </p>
<p>Sweeny, Trumka and Chavez-Thompson are working to rebuild the
labor movement through major organizing initiatives, the creation
of a powerful grassroots political movement of working people and
diversifying the leadership. </p>
<p>At the budget rally, other speakers will include Democratic
House Leader Richard Gephardt; Marion Wright Edeleman, president
of the Children's Defense Fund; and leaders from consumer,
farmer, senior, Latino and other organizations. </p>
<p>Working people, seniors, students and others would be hit hard
under the Republican budget plan, which cuts Medicare by $270
billion, slashes job safety and health, cuts education and other
programs working families rely on, all to give a $245 billion tax
cut to the wealthy.</p>
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a
href="../index.htm">Public Documents Page</a> | <a
