<title>PR 11/02/95 NAFTA Panel Discusses Sony Labor Violations</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>MEDIA ADVISORY                                         CONTACT: David Kameras
November 2, 1995                                                (202)637-5017
</pre>
<h3 align="center">NAFTA Panel Discusses SONY Labor Violations </h3>
<p>As a result of high-level meetings between Mexican and U.S.
Labor Department officials, experts in the field of labor
relations from Mexico, the U.S. and Canada will meet in San
Antonio on November 8 to discuss workers' rights violations that
took place at Sony facilities in Nuevo Laredo. Maquiladora
workers from the Sony plants and labor activists from the United
States will be present to discuss their case against Sony and the
Mexican government. Attorneys for the Sony workers have charged
Mexican authorities with complicity in violating the workers'
rights. </p>
<p>The panel discussions will be held on November 8 at the Hyatt
Regency Hotel, 123 Losoya Street, San Antonio, Texas, from 9:00
a.m. to 5:15 p.m. The Sony workers and labor activists from
Mexico, the U.S. and Canada will hold a press conference at 1:00
p.m.</p>
