<title>PR 11/01/95 AFL-CIO President Makes Staff Appointments</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<pre>For Immediate Release                           Contact: Candice Johnson
November 1, 1995                                            202/637-5010
</pre>
<h3 align="center">Federation President Makes Top Staff
Appointments </h3>
<p>In a meeting with all federation staff, newly elected AFL-CIO
President John J. Sweeney today named several individuals to top
staff positions at the federation. </p>
<p>Robert W. Welsh was named executive assistant to Sweeney. He
had held that position at the Service Employees, serving during
Sweeney's 15-year tenure as president of that union. </p>
<p>Brad Burton was named executive assistant to
SecretaryTreasurer Richard Trumka. Burton held that position at
the Mine Workers. </p>
<p>Arlene Holt will serve as executive assistant to AFL-CIO
executive vice president Linda Chavez-Thompson. Holt most
recently had been serving as AFSCME's national union area
director for California. </p>
<p>Jon Hiatt was named the federation's new general counsel, a
position he held at SEIU. </p>
<p>Denise Mitchell will serve as special assistant to the
president for public affairs. She had held that position at SEIU
and also is a partner at Abernathy and Mitchell, an advocacy and
public affairs firm. </p>
<p>Gerald Shea was named an assistant to the president to oversee
the transition and with responsibilities for government affairs.
Shea, for the past two years, had served as executive assistant
to former AFL-CIO President Tom Donahue. Earlier, he headed
SEIU's health care division and served as assistant to the SEIU
president for government affairs.</p>
