<head>
<title>PR 08/23/95 AFL-CIO Officers Schedule Whirlwind Tour in Los Angeles</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>Media advisory Contact: Candice Johnson<br>
August 23, 1995 at 202/637-5010<br>
<br>
<br>
Top AFL-CIO Officers Schedule Whirlwind Tour in Los Angeles<br>
<br>
<br>
AFL-CIO President Tom Donahue is in Los Angeles today,<br>
Wednesday, Aug. 23, the start of a two-day schedule that includes<br>
a working session with local organizers from the innovative L.A.<br>
MAP project and a meeting with several of the Thai workers who were<br>
enslaved in an El Monte sweatshop.<br>
<br>
Donahue will be joined at these Wednesday events by AFL-CIO<br>
Secretary-Treasurer Barbara Easterling, the pioneering first woman<br>
of American labor.<br>
<br>
The events, all open to reporters, will be held at these<br>
locations: <br>
<br>
3:30 p.m. L.A. MAP organizing meeting <br>
3363 East Gage Avenue<br>
Belle, California <br>
213/585-4596<br>
<br>
<br>
5 p.m. Meeting with Thai workers and community supporters<br>
UNITE local union hall<br>
675 South Parkview<br>
Los Angeles, Calif. <br>
213/380-5498<br>
<br>
On Thursday, Aug. 24, Donahue will meet with delegates<br>
attending a California AFL-CIO conference in a forum on the future<br>
with Service Employees President John J. Sweeney. The session will<br>
begin at 10 a.m. at the Biltmore Hotel, Los Angeles. <br>
<br>
<br>
###<br>
<br>
For more information contact David Sickler at 213/387-1974, and<br>
Candice Johnson, beginning Wednesday afternoon at the Biltmore<br>
Hotel, 213/624-1011.</p>
