<head>
<title>PR 07/12/95 Budget Cuts Show Contempt for Workers, AFL-CIO Says </title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>For Immediate Release                            Contact: Rex Hardesty<br>
July 12, 1995                                             202/637-5010<br>
<br>
<br>
          Budget Cuts Show Contempt for Workers, AFL-CIO Says<br>
<br>
<br>
AFL-CIO Secretary-Treasurer Tom Donahue made the following comment<br>
on budget cuts by the House appropriations subcommittee:<br>
<br>
      House Republicans today once again demonstrated their contempt<br>
for working men and women.<br>
<br>
      At a time when wages and benefits are falling and when workers<br>
need a real voice on the job more than ever, the House<br>
Appropriations Subcommittee took a meat cleaver to the budget of<br>
the National Labor Relations Board, the agency charged with<br>
enforcing the legal rights of American workers to form unions.<br>
Worse still, in the guise of appropriating, the Republicans voted<br>
to stall the Labor Board's program of seeking injunctions for<br>
workers whose rights are violated.<br>
<br>
      While tens of thousands of workers are killed or maimed each<br>
year as a result of occupational accidents or occupational diseases<br>
and millions of workers are injured on the job, the House<br>
Republicans voted to slash spending on enforcement of the<br>
Occupational Safety and Health Act by one-third.<br>
<br>
      And at a time when education and training is more and more<br>
urgent for the workers of today and tomorrow, the House Republicans<br>
voted to kill or starve critical educational and training programs.<br>
<br>
      The crisis confronting America's middle class is caused by too<br>
much corporate power -- not too little. The solution lies in giving<br>
workers more of a voice in the workplace, not in taking away their<br>
democratic rights.<br>
<br>
      The AFL-CIO will continue to fight the Republican attempts to<br>
destroy the laws and programs on which working families depend.<br>
Neither we, nor the working men and women we represent, will forget<br>
the culprits who have struck this blow at working Americans.</p>
<p align=center><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a href="/publ/publhome.html">Public Documents Page</a></p>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; AFL-CIO</p>
</body>

</html>
