<head>
<title>PR 06/28/95 Trade Union Leaders to Press Trade Ministers on Worker Rights</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>For immediate release Contact: Candice Johnson<br>
June 28, 1995 at 202/637-5010<br>
<br>
<br>
Trade Union Leaders to Press Trade Ministers on Worker Rights<br>
<br>
AFL-CIO Secretary-Treasurer Tom Donahue will represent U.S. workers at the Labor<br>
Summit of the Americas, which will open at 9 a.m, Thursday, June 29 in Denver, at the<br>
Executive Tower Inn. <br>
<br>
The labor summit will bring together trade union leaders from 20 countries in the<br>
Western Hemisphere, representing more than 40 million workers, in a unanimous call for<br>
worker rights to be included in hemispheric trade agreements. The session will be held the day<br>
before trade ministers meet in Denver on the proposed Free Trade Agreement of the Americas. <br>
<br>
Highlights of the schedule:<br>
<br>
9 a.m. Donahue and Luis Anderson, general secretary, ORIT.<br>
<br>
9:30 a.m. Working sessions on regional efforts and worker rights.<br>
<br>
1 p.m. Lunch session, with U.S. Trade Representative Mickey Kantor and<br>
Chilean Labor Minister Jorge Arrate MacNiven.<br>
<br>
3 p.m. NAFTA and Chile<br>
<br>
4:30 p.m. U.S. Labor Secretary Robert B. Reich<br>
<br>
<br>
All sessions are open to reporters.<br>
<br>
For interview requests and media availability, please contact Candice Johnson, AFL-CIO<br>
Information Department, at 202/637-5010, and beginning June 28, at the labor summit press<br>
room, 303/685-4908, or at the Executive Tower Inn at 303/571-0300. The Executive Tower<br>
Inn is located at 1405 Curtis Street, Denver.</p>
<p align=center><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a href="/publ/publhome.html">Public Documents Page</a></p>
