<head>
<title>PR 05/05/95 Economic Slowdown Trend Is Clear. </title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>PRESS ADVISORY                       CONTACT: Michael Byrne<br>
May 5, 1995                                  of the AFL-CIO<br>
                                               202/637-5010<br>
<br>
             ECONOMIC SLOWDOWN TREND IS CLEAR<br>
<br>
<br>
     While seasonal adjustment may account for some of<br>
the dramatic 0.3 percent rise in April unemployment, &quot;the<br>
direction is clear,&quot; said AFL-CIO economist Markley<br>
Roberts. &quot;There is an economic slowdown under way and it<br>
is reasonable and logical to see in this the continuing<br>
bite of Federal Reserve slow-growth, anti-inflation<br>
policies.&quot;<br>
<br>
     For further information, contact Roberts at 202/637-<br>
5171.</p>
