<head>
<title>SP 12/08/95 Sweeney at Hillhaven Nursing Home</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<pre>                       Remarks by John J. Sweeney
                           President, AFL-CIO
</pre>
<h3 align=center>Hillhaven Rally December 8, 1995 San Francisco </h3>
<p>Brothers and sisters, we are here today to deliver a message to the Hillhaven Corporation. </p>
<p>We are here today to deliver a message to every for-profit hospital, HMO, home care agency and 
nursing home chain in California. </p>
<p>We are here today to deliver a message to every elected official and community leader in California 
and to every woman and man in this great state who believes in decency and dignity and justice. </p>
<p>Our message is: we will not give in to corporate greed. </p>
<p>And I am here to deliver another message. It's a message to the families of the courageous 
Vencor/Hillhaven workers who have given their hearts and their hands to build this giant nursing 
home chain. </p>
<p>Our message is: the AFL-CIO will stand beside you in your hour of need. </p>
<p>This is not a strike about slashing wages; this is a strike about putting profits before patients. </p>
<p>This isn't a strike about benefits; this is about permanently replacing workers who exercised their 
right to strike for ONE DAY ..... the first workers in the Bay area in recent memory to be 
permanently replaced. </p>
<p>This isn't a strike about working conditions; it's a strike about squeezing the last ounce of 
productivity out of workers and then throwing them in the street. </p>
<p>What's wrong with this picture: </p>
<p>Productivity is up. Profits are up. So the company wants to squeeze a little more out of low-wage 
women workers. </p>
<p>I'll tell you what's wrong with this picture --- there's no respect for workers or the jobs they do or 
the contribution they make, and this strike is not going to end until we regain that respect. </p>
<p>You are not alone: your story is being played out in every workplace in America ---productivity up, 
profits up, workers down. </p>
<p>What you are doing here is an inspiration to other unions and to other workers across our country 
--- we've learned the hard way that an injury to one is an injury to all. </p>
<p>And that is why 13 million members of the AFL-CIO are committed to you and to your cause --- 
we are going to start proving that a victory for one is a victory for all! </p>
<p>We're going to do whatever it takes, work as hard as it takes, and stick with it as long as it takes to 
help Hillhaven workers win the respect you have earned and deserve. </p>
<p>And in doing so, we will send a massive message to every greedy, short-sighted employer in this 
country: honor American work, honor American workers, honor American working families. </p>
<p>America works because we do, and when we stop working, America stops working!</p>
<p align=center><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a href="../publhome.html">Public Documents Page</a></p>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; AFL-CIO</p>
</body>

