<html>
<head>
<title>SP 11/18/95 Sweeney to CWA Bell Atlantic Rally</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<h3 align="center">Remarks by John J. Sweeney, President AFL-CIO </h3>
<h3 align="center">CWA Bell Atlantic Rally November 18, 1995
Baltimore </h3>
<p>Brothers and sisters, we are here today to deliver a message
to Bell Atlantic Corporation. </p>
<p>We are here today to deliver a message to the United States
Congress, the Department of Labor and the National Labor
Relations Board. </p>
<p>We are here today to deliver a message to every woman and man
in New Jersey, Pennsylvania, Delaware, Maryland, Virginia, West
Virginia and the District of Columbia who believes in decency and
dignity and justice. </p>
<p>Our message is: we will not give in to corporate greed. </p>
<p>Not here on the east coast with Bell Atlantic workers, not on
the west coast with the courageous Boeing strikers, not in the
heartland with the Caterpillar strikers, the Staley strikers or
the Detroit News strikers. </p>
<p>I am also here to personally deliver another message. </p>
<p>It's a message from the 13 million members of the AFL-CIO to
the families of 34,000 CWA members who built this giant company
with their sweat and their blood and their lives. </p>
<p>Our message is: we will stand beside you in your hour of need. </p>
<p>This is not an ordinary labor-management confrontation about
wages, working conditions and benefits. </p>
<p>It is an extraordinary confrontation about union-busting and
job destruction. </p>
<p>This isn't a union campaign about union issues. </p>
<p>It is a workers crusade to protect the future of their
families. </p>
<p>This isn't even a rally to protest bad faith bargaining and
the suspension of 6,000 loyal employees for exercising their
legal rights. </p>
<p>It is a rally to protest squeezing the highest productivity in
the telecommunications industry out of 34,000 workers and then
attempting to abandon them like so much roadkill on the
information super highway. </p>
<p>What's wrong with this picture: </p>
<p>In 1994, Bell Atlantic earned profits of $1.4 billion on
revenues of $13.8 billion. </p>
<p>Over the past five years, Bell Atlantic revenues have grown 20
percent and profits have grown 30 percent. </p>
<p>Last year, Bell Atlantic awarded stock options to CEO Ray
Smith that will be worth $82 million dollars in just 10 years! </p>
<p>And with the impending passage of the Telecommunications Act,
Bell Atlantic is to take off like a rocket into profit paradise. </p>
<p>But the company wants to reward the retirees responsible for
past performance by making them pay for health benefits. </p>
<p>And to reward workers responsible for current and future
performance by slashing wages and benefits and subcontracting out
their jobs. -more- </p>
<p>I'll tell you what's wrong with this picture --- there's no
RESPECT for workers or the jobs they do or the contribution they
make, and this confrontation is not going to end until you are
granted that respect. </p>
<p>You are not alone in your struggle. </p>
<p>Your story is being played out in every workplace in America
---productivity up, profits up, workers down. </p>
<p>But the methods you are using to bring this employer to
justice are unique. </p>
<p>You are plotting a course of new unionism for every member of
every union in America to follow and all of us will benefit from
your efforts. </p>
<p>What you are doing here is an inspiration to other unions and
to other workers across our country --- we've learned the hard
way that an injury to one is an injury to all. </p>
<p>And that is why 13 million members of the AFL-CIO are
committed to you and to your cause --- we are going to start
proving that a victory for one is a victory for all! </p>
<p>To your great president, Morty Bahr, and to Pete Catucci,
Vince Maisano, Jan Pierce and to every one of you, I bring a
commitment from the &quot;New Voice for American Workers:&quot;<br>
We're going to spend whatever it takes, work as hard as it takes,
and stick with it as long as it takes to help CWA Bell Atlantic
members win the respect and the job security you have earned and
that you deserve. </p>
<p>And in doing so, we will send a massive message to every
greedy, short-sighted employer in this country: honor American
work, honor American workers, honor American working families. </p>
<p>America works because we do, and when we stop working, America
stops working! </p>
<p>-end- </p>
<p>For further information, weekend: Denise Mitchell (202)
362-3745</p>
